1)What is an Angualr?
A) Angular is the JS binding frame which will help to  bind the View(HTML UI) and Model(JS) together and also it helps to build 
SPA by using the concept of Routing.It also had lot of other features like HTTP,Dependency Injections etc.

2)WHAT IS DIFFERENCE BETWEEN ANGULARJS VS ANGULAR?
A) AngularJs :
   Language: Java script
    Architecure: Controller
    Mobile Compliant: No
    CLI: No
    SEO: No
    Server Side: NO

Angular :
   Language: Type script
    Architecure: Component
    Mobile Compliant: yes (By using ionix we can make good mobile application)
    CLI: yes
    SEO: yes
    Server Side: yes

3)WHAT ARE DIRECTIVES IN ANGULAR?
A) Directives are the angular syntax inside the HTML they go and change the behaviour of HTML DOM.
 In the HTML page:
 <input [(ngModel)]= "value" type= "text">
<div>{{value}}</div>
<div [hidden] = "Hide()">Hello</div>

(Note: From the above example ngmodle, value, hidden all are the directives which changes the behaviourof HTML DOM)

4) what are the different types of angular Directives?
A)We have 3 types of Directives:
*Structural Directive:Structural directives changes the structure of  HTML DOM elemnets.they add the new element in the DOM or remove a element in DOM.
*Attribute Directive: Attribute Directive does not change the structure but it changes the behaviour of the HTML DOM.
<div [hidden] = "Hide()">Hello</div>

*Component Directive:A component directive is like a customized user control which has own template.

5)what is the use of NPM and Node_Modules_folder?
A)NPM stands for Node Pakcage manager. NPM is a pacakge manager which installs the js frameworks.Node_module is the folder where all
the packages are installed.
npm install Angular

6) What is the imporatnce of Package.json File?
A)It has all the Javascript references needed for a project. So rather than installing one package at a time we can install all the packages in one go.

7) What is TypeScript?
A)Typescript is the superset of JS . It  adds types to JS.It gives a nice object-oriented programming environment which conerts to javascript.
Example: Without Typescript
Var x = 0;
X++;
X="shiv";

Example:  Typescript
Var x:number= 0;
X++;
X="shiv";

8) Importance of Angular CLI?
A) Command line interface. It help to create the readymade angular project template. To install the CLI we should use 
npm install @angular/cli
ng new myapp   (creates a project template)

9) Expain the importance of component and modules?
A) A component is the central point which goes and bind view and module or css and module. Component is the place in the angular where we write the binding code.
Module: A module groups angular components.

10) Expalin the importance of decorater in the Angular? or what is metadata or annotations?
A) A decorater defines what type of the angular class it is. For example: If you use @component on the top of class then it says 
it is  a angular component. If you use @ngmodule on top of calss it says it is angular module.

11) what is Template in angular?
Template is the HTML view of angular in which we can write direcives.There are two ways of defing template one is inline and other is
seperate html file. We can link the template with the @component decorater.













